aima.core.logic.propositional.kb.data

Class Literal

  • java.lang.Object
    • aima.core.logic.propositional.kb.data.Literal

  • public class Literal
extends java.lang.Object
    Artificial Intelligence A Modern Approach (3rd Edition): page 244.

    A literal is either an atomic sentence (a positive literal) or a negated atomic sentence (a negative literal). In propositional logic the atomic sentences consist of a single proposition symbol. In addition, a literal as implemented is immutable.
    Author:
    Ciaran O'Reilly
